<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 1 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch1">1. Project Overview</h2>
  
  <p><strong>FaceInsight</strong> is a privacy-focused, real-time facial analysis web application designed for retail stores, cafés, and service environments. It uses browser-based machine learning to detect faces from a webcam feed and analyze customer emotions, age groups, and gender — all without transmitting or storing any facial images.</p>
  
  <p>The system provides a comprehensive analytics dashboard with sentiment trends, demographic breakdowns, and actionable insights to help businesses understand customer engagement and satisfaction levels.</p>
  
  <h3>Key Highlights</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>100% Browser-Based ML</strong> — No server-side processing of video or images</li>
    <li><strong>Privacy by Design</strong> — No facial images are stored or transmitted to any server</li>
    <li><strong>Real-Time Analytics</strong> — Live dashboards with multiple interactive chart types</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-Face Support</strong> — Simultaneously analyze multiple faces in a single frame</li>
    <li><strong>7 Emotion Classes</strong> — Happy, Sad, Angry, Neutral, Surprised, Fearful, Disgusted</li>
    <li><strong>Responsive Design</strong> — Works seamlessly on desktop and tablet devices</li>
    <li><strong>Data Export &amp; Management</strong> — Export analytics as JSON, clear data on demand</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 2 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch2">2. Problem Statement</h2>
  
  <p>Traditional customer feedback mechanisms — such as surveys, online reviews, and physical feedback forms — suffer from inherently low response rates and significant selection bias. Customers who are extremely satisfied or dissatisfied are overrepresented, while the majority of customers provide no feedback at all. This creates a distorted view of actual customer sentiment.</p>
  
  <p>Businesses operating physical locations such as cafés, retail stores, and service centers lack real-time visibility into customer emotions and demographics. By the time negative trends are identified through conventional methods, the damage to customer satisfaction and revenue has already occurred.</p>
  
  <p>Existing facial analysis solutions on the market raise significant privacy concerns because they transmit facial data to cloud-based servers for processing. This approach conflicts with growing privacy regulations (GDPR, CCPA) and consumer expectations around data protection.</p>
  
  <h3>FaceInsight addresses these challenges by providing:</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Real-time, passive customer sentiment monitoring</strong> — No customer participation required</li>
    <li><strong>Complete privacy preservation</strong> — All ML processing occurs client-side in the browser</li>
    <li><strong>Actionable demographic and emotional analytics</strong> — Visualized through interactive dashboards</li>
    <li><strong>Zero friction for customers</strong> — No forms, no surveys, no opt-in needed</li>
    <li><strong>Regulatory compliance</strong> — Only anonymized aggregate statistics are stored</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 3 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch3">3. Objectives</h2>
  
  <p>The primary objectives of this project are:</p>
  
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Design and implement</strong> a real-time face detection system using browser-based machine learning technologies (TensorFlow.js / face-api.js)</li>
    <li><strong>Classify customer emotions</strong> into 7 distinct categories (Happy, Sad, Angry, Neutral, Surprised, Fearful, Disgusted) with associated confidence scores</li>
    <li><strong>Predict demographic attributes</strong> including age group (Child, Teen, Adult, Senior) and gender from facial features</li>
    <li><strong>Build a comprehensive analytics dashboard</strong> for visualizing sentiment trends, demographic distributions, and temporal patterns</li>
    <li><strong>Ensure complete privacy</strong> by processing all video frames locally in the browser and storing only anonymized statistical data</li>
    <li><strong>Create an intuitive, responsive user interface</strong> suitable for deployment in retail and hospitality environments</li>
    <li><strong>Implement data management features</strong> including export capabilities and data clearing functionality</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 4 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch4">4. Features</h2>
  
  <h3>4.1 Real-Time Face Detection</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Live webcam feed with face bounding box overlays</li>
    <li>Multi-face simultaneous detection and analysis</li>
    <li>Configurable detection interval (100ms to 2000ms)</li>
    <li>Camera device selection support for multi-camera setups</li>
    <li>Visual indicators for active detection status</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>4.2 Emotion Recognition</h3>
  <p>The system classifies facial expressions into 7 emotion categories using deep learning:</p>
  
  <table>
    <tr><th>Emotion</th><th>Emoji</th><th>Sentiment Category</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Happy</td><td>😊</td><td>Positive</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Surprised</td><td>😲</td><td>Positive</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Neutral</td><td>😐</td><td>Neutral</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Sad</td><td>😢</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Angry</td><td>😠</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Fearful</td><td>😨</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Disgusted</td><td>🤢</td><td>Negative</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h3>4.3 Demographic Analysis</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Age Groups:</strong> Child (0–12), Teen (13–19), Adult (20–59), Senior (60+)</li>
    <li><strong>Gender:</strong> Male, Female</li>
    <li>Confidence percentages provided for each prediction</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>4.4 Analytics Dashboard</h3>
  <p>The dashboard provides the following visualizations:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Total Faces Analyzed</strong> — Running counter with real-time updates</li>
    <li><strong>Sentiment Score</strong> — Composite gauge ranging from 0 to 100</li>
    <li><strong>Emotion Distribution</strong> — Animated pie chart showing emotion proportions</li>
    <li><strong>Sentiment Trend</strong> — Hourly line chart tracking positive, negative, and neutral sentiment</li>
    <li><strong>Age Group Distribution</strong> — Bar chart of demographic age groups</li>
    <li><strong>Emotion by Gender</strong> — Grouped bar chart correlating emotions with gender</li>
    <li><strong>Peak Unhappy Times</strong> — Cards highlighting the top 3 hours with most negative sentiment</li>
    <li><strong>Sentiment Gauge</strong> — Visual 0–100 gauge with color-coded zones</li>
    <li><strong>Time Range Filters</strong> — Today, This Week, This Month, All Time</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>4.5 Settings &amp; Data Management</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Camera device selection dropdown</li>
    <li>Detection interval adjustment slider</li>
    <li>Toggle for enabling/disabling database persistence</li>
    <li>Export all analytics data as JSON file</li>
    <li>Clear all stored data with confirmation dialog</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 5 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch5">5. System Architecture</h2>
  
  <h3>5.1 High-Level Architecture Diagram</h3>
  
  <div class="architecture-box">┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐
│                    Client Browser                       │
│                                                         │
│  ┌──────────┐    ┌───────────────┐    ┌──────────────┐  │
│  │  Webcam   │──▶│  face-api.js  │──▶│  React UI    │  │
│  │  Stream   │    │ (TensorFlow.js)│   │  Components  │  │
│  └──────────┘    └───────┬───────┘    └──────┬───────┘  │
│                          │                    │          │
│                  ┌───────▼───────┐            │          │
│                  │  Anonymized   │            │          │
│                  │  Data Only    │            │          │
│                  │  (no images)  │            │          │
│                  └───────┬───────┘            │          │
└──────────────────────────┼────────────────────┼──────────┘
                           │                    │
                   ┌───────▼────────────────────▼──────┐
                   │         Firebase Firestore         │
                   │     (Anonymized Statistics Only)   │
                   │                                    │
                   │  • emotion, confidence             │
                   │  • age_group, age_estimate          │
                   │  • gender, gender_confidence        │
                   │  • timestamp, session_id            │
                   └────────────────────────────────────┘</div>
  
  <h3>5.2 Data Flow</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Video Capture</strong> — The browser captures video frames from the user's webcam via the WebRTC API (<code>navigator.mediaDevices.getUserMedia</code>)</li>
    <li><strong>Local ML Processing</strong> — face-api.js (built on TensorFlow.js) processes each video frame entirely within the browser's JavaScript engine using WebGL acceleration</li>
    <li><strong>Feature Extraction</strong> — ML models extract emotion classification, age estimation, and gender prediction from detected faces</li>
    <li><strong>Anonymization</strong> — Only statistical labels and confidence scores are retained; no facial landmarks, embeddings, or pixel data leaves the processing pipeline</li>
    <li><strong>Storage</strong> — Anonymized records are persisted to Firebase Firestore as structured documents</li>
    <li><strong>Visualization</strong> — The dashboard queries stored data in real-time and renders interactive charts using the Recharts library</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h3>5.3 Component Architecture</h3>
  <p>The application follows a modular React component architecture with clear separation of concerns:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Pages</strong> — Top-level route components (Index, Analyze, Dashboard, Settings)</li>
    <li><strong>Layout Components</strong> — Shared UI elements (Header, Navigation)</li>
    <li><strong>Feature Components</strong> — Domain-specific components (CameraView, FaceOverlay, Chart components)</li>
    <li><strong>UI Primitives</strong> — Reusable design-system components (Button, Card, Select, etc.)</li>
    <li><strong>Custom Hooks</strong> — Encapsulated business logic (useFaceDetection, useAnalytics)</li>
    <li><strong>Library Modules</strong> — Utility functions and ML wrapper (faceApi.ts, utils.ts)</li>
  </ul>
</div>

