<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch12">12. Installation &amp; Setup</h2>
  
  <h3>12.1 Prerequisites</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Node.js</strong> version 18.x or higher</li>
    <li><strong>npm</strong> or <strong>bun</strong> package manager</li>
    <li>A modern web browser with WebRTC and WebGL support (Chrome, Firefox, or Edge)</li>
    <li>A webcam (built-in or external USB)</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>12.2 Installation Steps</h3>
  
  <pre>
# 1. Clone the repository
git clone &lt;repository-url&gt;
cd faceinsight

# 2. Install dependencies
npm install

# 3. Download ML models (if not already present in public/models/)
node download-models.js
# On Windows PowerShell:
# ./download-models.ps1

# 4. Start development server
npm run dev

# 5. Open in browser
# Navigate to http://localhost:5173</pre>
  
  <h3>12.3 Required Model Files</h3>
  <p>The following files must exist in the <code>public/models/</code> directory:</p>
  
  <pre>
public/models/
├── tiny_face_detector_model-shard1
├── tiny_face_detector_model-weights_manifest.json
├── face_landmark_68_model-shard1
├── face_landmark_68_model-weights_manifest.json
├── face_expression_model-shard1
├── face_expression_model-weights_manifest.json
├── age_gender_model-shard1
├── age_gender_model-weights_manifest.json
├── face_recognition_model-shard1
├── face_recognition_model-shard2
└── face_recognition_model-weights_manifest.json</pre>
  
  <h3>12.4 Build for Production</h3>
  <pre>
# Create optimized production build
npm run build

# Preview production build locally
npm run preview</pre>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 13 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch13">13. Configuration</h2>
  
  <h3>13.1 Firebase Configuration</h3>
  <p>Firebase is initialized in <code>src/integrations/firebase/client.ts</code> with the following services:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Firestore</strong> — NoSQL document database for storing anonymized analytics</li>
    <li><strong>Analytics</strong> — Firebase Analytics for application usage tracking</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>13.2 Runtime Configuration (Settings Page)</h3>
  
  <table>
    <tr><th>Setting</th><th>Default Value</th><th>Range</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Detection Interval</td><td>500ms</td><td>100ms – 2000ms</td><td>Time between detection cycles</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Save to Database</td><td>Enabled</td><td>On / Off</td><td>Toggle Firestore persistence</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Camera Device</td><td>First available</td><td>Device list</td><td>Select video input device</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h3>13.3 Performance Tuning</h3>
  <p>The detection interval directly affects both accuracy and CPU usage:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>100ms</strong> — Highest frequency, ~10 detections/second. High CPU usage. Best for high-traffic environments.</li>
    <li><strong>500ms</strong> (default) — Balanced performance. ~2 detections/second. Recommended for most use cases.</li>
    <li><strong>2000ms</strong> — Lowest frequency, ~0.5 detections/second. Minimal CPU impact. Suitable for low-traffic environments.</li>
  </ul>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 14 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch14">14. Usage Guide</h2>
  
  <h3>14.1 Starting Live Analysis</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Analyze</strong> page using the navigation header</li>
    <li>Click the <strong>"Start Analysis"</strong> button</li>
    <li>The browser will request camera access permission — click <strong>"Allow"</strong></li>
    <li>Face detection begins automatically at the configured detection interval</li>
    <li>Each detected face displays a color-coded bounding box with:
      <ul>
        <li>Emotion emoji and label with confidence percentage</li>
        <li>Predicted age group</li>
        <li>Predicted gender</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>A green "Live" indicator confirms active detection</li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Stop Analysis"</strong> to end the session and release the camera</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h3>14.2 Viewing Analytics</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to the <strong>Dashboard</strong> page</li>
    <li>Use the time range selector to filter data: Today / This Week / This Month / All Time</li>
    <li>Charts update in real-time via Firestore subscriptions as new detections are recorded</li>
    <li>Review the stat cards for key metrics: total analyzed faces, sentiment score, positive and negative percentages</li>
    <li>Check the <strong>"Peak Unhappy Times"</strong> section to identify hours with the most negative sentiment</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h3>14.3 Exporting Data</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Export Data (JSON)"</strong></li>
    <li>A JSON file downloads containing all stored analytics records</li>
    <li>The exported file can be imported into Excel, Python (pandas), or any data analysis tool</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h3>14.4 Clearing Data</h3>
  <ol>
    <li>Navigate to <strong>Settings</strong></li>
    <li>Click <strong>"Clear All Data"</strong></li>
    <li>Confirm the action in the browser dialog</li>
    <li>All stored analytics are permanently and irreversibly deleted from Firestore</li>
  </ol>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 15 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch15">15. API &amp; Hooks Reference</h2>
  
  <h3>15.1 <code>useFaceDetection(options)</code></h3>
  <p>The primary hook for managing webcam access and face detection logic.</p>
  
  <h4>Options</h4>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>autoStart</td><td>boolean</td><td>false</td><td>Auto-start detection on component mount</td></tr>
    <tr><td>detectionInterval</td><td>number</td><td>500</td><td>Milliseconds between detection cycles</td></tr>
    <tr><td>saveToDatabase</td><td>boolean</td><td>true</td><td>Whether to persist results to Firestore</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h4>Return Values</h4>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Property</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>isLoading</td><td>boolean</td><td>True while ML models are being loaded</td></tr>
    <tr><td>error</td><td>string | null</td><td>Error message if camera or model loading fails</td></tr>
    <tr><td>isRunning</td><td>boolean</td><td>True when detection is actively running</td></tr>
    <tr><td>detections</td><td>FaceDetection[]</td><td>Array of faces detected in current frame</td></tr>
    <tr><td>modelsReady</td><td>boolean</td><td>True when all ML models are loaded</td></tr>
    <tr><td>totalAnalyzed</td><td>number</td><td>Cumulative count of faces analyzed</td></tr>
    <tr><td>startDetection</td><td>(deviceId?) =&gt; Promise&lt;boolean&gt;</td><td>Start camera and detection loop</td></tr>
    <tr><td>stopDetection</td><td>() =&gt; void</td><td>Stop detection and release camera</td></tr>
    <tr><td>setVideoElement</td><td>(el) =&gt; void</td><td>Attach video element reference</td></tr>
    <tr><td>videoRef</td><td>RefObject&lt;HTMLVideoElement&gt;</td><td>Reference to the video element</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h3>15.2 <code>useAnalytics(timeRange)</code></h3>
  <p>Hook for fetching and computing dashboard analytics from Firestore.</p>
  
  <h4>Parameters</h4>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Parameter</th><th>Type</th><th>Values</th></tr>
    <tr><td>timeRange</td><td>TimeRange</td><td>'today' | 'week' | 'month' | 'all'</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h4>Computed Statistics</h4>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Stat</th><th>Type</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>total</td><td>number</td><td>Total records in time range</td></tr>
    <tr><td>emotionCounts</td><td>Record&lt;string, number&gt;</td><td>Count per emotion</td></tr>
    <tr><td>ageGroupCounts</td><td>Record&lt;string, number&gt;</td><td>Count per age group</td></tr>
    <tr><td>genderCounts</td><td>Record&lt;string, number&gt;</td><td>Count per gender</td></tr>
    <tr><td>sentimentScore</td><td>number</td><td>0–100 composite score</td></tr>
    <tr><td>positive</td><td>number</td><td>Count of positive emotions</td></tr>
    <tr><td>negative</td><td>number</td><td>Count of negative emotions</td></tr>
    <tr><td>neutral</td><td>number</td><td>Count of neutral emotions</td></tr>
    <tr><td>hourlyData</td><td>Record&lt;string, {...}&gt;</td><td>Hourly sentiment breakdown</td></tr>
    <tr><td>emotionByGender</td><td>Record&lt;...&gt;</td><td>Emotion distribution per gender</td></tr>
    <tr><td>peakUnhappyHours</td><td>{hour, count}[]</td><td>Top 3 negative sentiment hours</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h3>15.3 FaceDetection Interface</h3>
  <pre>
interface FaceDetection {
  id: string;                  // Unique identifier
  box: {
    x: number;                 // Bounding box x position
    y: number;                 // Bounding box y position
    width: number;             // Bounding box width
    height: number;            // Bounding box height
  };
  emotion: string;             // Dominant emotion label
  emotionConfidence: number;   // 0.0 – 1.0
  age: number;                 // Estimated age in years
  ageGroup: string;            // "Child" | "Teen" | "Adult" | "Senior"
  gender: string;              // "male" | "female"
  genderConfidence: number;    // 0.0 – 1.0
}</pre>
  
  <h3>15.4 Utility Functions</h3>
  <table>
    <tr><th>Function</th><th>Input</th><th>Output</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    <tr><td>loadModels()</td><td>—</td><td>Promise&lt;void&gt;</td><td>Loads all face-api.js ML models</td></tr>
    <tr><td>isModelsLoaded()</td><td>—</td><td>boolean</td><td>Check if models are ready</td></tr>
    <tr><td>detectFaces(video)</td><td>HTMLVideoElement</td><td>Promise&lt;FaceDetection[]&gt;</td><td>Run detection on video frame</td></tr>
    <tr><td>getAgeGroup(age)</td><td>number</td><td>string</td><td>Map age to group label</td></tr>
    <tr><td>getEmotionEmoji(emotion)</td><td>string</td><td>string</td><td>Get emoji for emotion</td></tr>
    <tr><td>getEmotionColor(emotion)</td><td>string</td><td>string</td><td>Get HSL color for emotion</td></tr>
  </table>
</div>

<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 16 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch16">16. Security &amp; Privacy</h2>
  
  <h3>16.1 Threat Model &amp; Mitigations</h3>
  
  <table>
    <tr><th>Threat</th><th>Risk Level</th><th>Mitigation</th></tr>
    <tr><td>Face image exfiltration</td><td>Critical</td><td>All ML processing is client-side; no image data enters any network request</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Identity tracking via biometrics</td><td>High</td><td>No facial embeddings, descriptors, or landmark geometry is stored</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Data re-identification</td><td>Medium</td><td>Only categorical labels stored; mathematically impossible to reconstruct faces</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Unauthorized data access</td><td>Medium</td><td>Firebase security rules; user-controlled data export and deletion</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Session correlation</td><td>Low</td><td>Random UUID per session; no cookies, login, or device fingerprinting</td></tr>
    <tr><td>Man-in-the-middle attacks</td><td>Low</td><td>HTTPS enforced for all Firestore communication</td></tr>
  </table>
  
  <h3>16.2 Privacy Compliance</h3>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>GDPR Alignment</strong> — No personal data is collected; only anonymous aggregate statistics are stored</li>
    <li><strong>Data Minimization</strong> — Only essential fields (emotion label, age group, gender) are persisted</li>
    <li><strong>Right to Deletion</strong> — One-click data clearing is available in the Settings page</li>
    <li><strong>Transparency</strong> — Privacy notices are prominently displayed on the landing page and analysis page</li>
    <li><strong>Purpose Limitation</strong> — Data is used exclusively for sentiment and demographic analytics</li>
  </ul>
  
  <h3>16.3 Security Best Practices Implemented</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>No server-side processing of sensitive media</li>
    <li>WebRTC camera streams are consumed locally only</li>
    <li>Firebase SDK handles authentication and transport encryption</li>
    <li>No third-party tracking scripts or advertising SDKs</li>
    <li>Content Security Policy compatible architecture</li>
  </ul>
</div>

