<!-- ==================== CHAPTER 18 ==================== -->
<div class="page-break">
  <h2 id="ch18">18. Limitations &amp; Future Work</h2>
  
  <h3>18.1 Current Limitations</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Lighting Sensitivity</strong> — Face detection accuracy decreases significantly in poor or uneven lighting conditions</li>
    <li><strong>Angle Dependency</strong> — Best results are achieved with near-frontal face orientation; extreme angles reduce detection rate</li>
    <li><strong>Age Estimation Variance</strong> — ML age predictions can have ±5–10 year error margins, particularly for younger and older faces</li>
    <li><strong>Browser Compatibility</strong> — Requires a modern browser with WebRTC (camera access) and WebGL (GPU acceleration) support</li>
    <li><strong>Single-Tab Operation</strong> — Running analysis in multiple browser tabs may cause camera resource conflicts</li>
    <li><strong>No User Authentication</strong> — The system operates with open access by design (suitable for educational/demo use)</li>
    <li><strong>Binary Gender Classification</strong> — The pre-trained model only predicts male/female, which does not represent the full gender spectrum</li>
    <li><strong>Cultural Bias</strong> — Pre-trained models may exhibit varying accuracy across different ethnic groups due to training data distribution</li>
  </ol>
  
  <h3>18.2 Future Enhancements</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Email/SMS Alerts</strong> — Notify store managers when negative sentiment exceeds configurable thresholds</li>
    <li><strong>PDF Report Generation</strong> — Automated daily/weekly summary reports with embedded charts</li>
    <li><strong>Period Comparison</strong> — Side-by-side comparison of sentiment metrics across different time periods</li>
    <li><strong>Heatmap Visualization</strong> — Time-of-day × day-of-week sentiment heatmap for pattern recognition</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-Camera Support</strong> — Monitor and analyze feeds from multiple cameras simultaneously</li>
    <li><strong>Offline Mode</strong> — Queue analytics locally using IndexedDB when network connectivity is unavailable</li>
    <li><strong>Custom Emotion Grouping</strong> — Allow users to define their own positive/negative/neutral categories</li>
    <li><strong>A/B Testing Integration</strong> — Correlate customer sentiment data with store layout or product changes</li>
    <li><strong>User Authentication</strong> — Add login system for multi-user deployments with role-based access</li>
    <li><strong>Progressive Web App (PWA)</strong> — Add service worker for offline capability and installable app experience</li>
  </ol>
</div>

